    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="46"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bryan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 205.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    249, of the 1st instant, transmitting copy of a note addressed to you by the
                    German minister to Brazil, requesting your cooperation in an endeavor to prevent
                    the enforcement of the Brazilian law forbidding the use of the Portuguese
                    language in trade-marks on articles of foreign manufacture.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have to say that you will follow the instructions sent to you by
                    cable and mail directing you to remonstrate against the law referred to.</p>
                <p>You will do this, however, independently of other diplomatic agents.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
